## Diagnosis

You're right — this is a recurring pattern where component implementation outpaces documentation. The playground (typically a `page.tsx` or story file) doesn't reflect the new `solid` variant, leaving consumers with no discoverable reference. This is **AP-072: Implementation–Documentation Drift**, compounded by the absence of any enforcement mechanism.

---

## Root Cause

There is no structural coupling between the component's variant definition and its playground registration. Variants live in the component file (or a `variants.ts` / `cva` config), and the playground is a completely separate file that requires **manual, human-remembered** updates. Nothing fails — no lint, no type error, no test — when the two fall out of sync.

---

## Fix

### Step 1 — Document the `solid` variant in the playground now

**File: `src/app/playground/navigation/page.tsx`**

```tsx
import { Navigation } from "@/components/navigation/Navigation";

// ─── Canonical appearance values ────────────────────────────────────────────
// This array is the single source of truth for playground coverage.
// Add every new variant here the moment you add it to the component.
const APPEARANCE_VARIANTS = [
  "default",
  "ghost",
  "solid",           // ← added
] as const satisfies NavigationAppearance[];   // type-checked against the union

// ─── Playground sections ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
export default function NavigationPlayground() {
  return (
    <main className="space-y-16 p-10">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Navigation — Playground</h1>

      {APPEARANCE_VARIANTS.map((appearance) => (
        <section key={appearance} className="space-y-4">
          <h2 className="text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
            appearance=&quot;{appearance}&quot;
          </h2>

          {/* Default state */}
          <Navigation appearance={appearance} items={SAMPLE_ITEMS} />

          {/* Active item */}
          <Navigation
            appearance={appearance}
            items={SAMPLE_ITEMS}
            activeHref="/work"
          />

          {/* Disabled item */}
          <Navigation
            appearance={appearance}
            items={SAMPLE_ITEMS_WITH_DISABLED}
          />
        </section>
      ))}
    </main>
  );
}
```

The `satisfies NavigationAppearance[]` constraint means **adding a variant to the component union without adding it here causes a compile error**, not a silent gap.

---

### Step 2 — Export the variant union from the component (if not already)

**File: `src/components/navigation/Navigation.tsx`**

```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority";

const navigationVariants = cva("...", {
  variants: {
    appearance: {
      default: "...",
      ghost:   "...",
      solid:   "bg-surface-solid text-on-solid ...",  // ← new
    },
  },
  defaultVariants: { appearance: "default" },
});

// ✅ Export the union so playground (and any consumer) can import it
export type NavigationAppearance = NonNullable<
  VariantProps<typeof navigationVariants>["appearance"]
>;
```

Now the playground's `satisfies NavigationAppearance[]` is structurally linked to the implementation.

---

### Step 3 — Add a lint rule to enforce this permanently

**File: `.eslintrc.cjs` (or `eslint.config.mjs`)**

```js
// eslint-plugin-local or eslint-plugin-no-restricted-syntax
{
  rules: {
    "no-restricted-syntax": [
      "error",
      {
        // Prevent exporting a new variant union without a corresponding
        // playground entry. Catches the file-save, not the PR review.
        //
        // Coarser version: flag any NavigationAppearance re-export
        // that doesn't appear in the playground file at CI time.
        // Use the companion check below instead for full coverage.
      },
    ],
  },
}
```

For a stronger check, add a **CI test**:

**File: `scripts/check-playground-coverage.ts`**

```ts
/**
 * Enforces: every exported *Appearance (or *Variant) union in /components
 * has a corresponding entry in the matching /playground page.
 *
 * Run: `pnpm check:playground` — also runs in CI via `lint` job.
 */
import { Project, SyntaxKind } from "ts-morph";

const project = new Project({ tsConfigFilePath: "./tsconfig.json" });

const componentFiles = project.getSourceFiles("src/components/**/*.tsx");

let exitCode = 0;

for (const file of componentFiles) {
  const typeAliases = file.getTypeAliases().filter((t) =>
    t.getName().endsWith("Appearance") || t.getName().endsWith("Variant")
  );

  for (const alias of typeAliases) {
    const componentName = file
      .getBaseNameWithoutExtension()
      .toLowerCase();

    const playgroundFile = project.getSourceFile(
      `src/app/playground/${componentName}/page.tsx`
    );

    if (!playgroundFile) {
      console.error(
        `❌  No playground found for ${file.getBaseName()} — expected src/app/playground/${componentName}/page.tsx`
      );
      exitCode = 1;
      continue;
    }

    // Collect string literals in the playground's APPEARANCE_VARIANTS array
    const literals = playgroundFile
      .getDescendantsOfKind(SyntaxKind.StringLiteral)
      .map((l) => l.getLiteralValue());

    // Resolve the union members from the type alias
    const checker = project.getTypeChecker();
    const type = checker.getTypeAtLocation(alias.getTypeNodeOrThrow());
    const members = type
      .getUnionTypes()
      .map((t) => t.getLiteralValue() as string);

    for (const member of members) {
      if (!literals.includes(member)) {
        console.error(
          `❌  "${member}" variant of ${alias.getName()} is not documented in the ${componentName} playground.`
        );
        exitCode = 1;
      }
    }
  }
}

if (exitCode === 0) console.log("✅  All variant playgrounds are current.");
process.exit(exitCode);
```

**File: `package.json`**

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "check:playground": "tsx scripts/check-playground-coverage.ts",
    "lint": "eslint . && pnpm check:playground"
  }
}
```

---

### Step 4 — Codify the rule in the contribution guide

**File: `CONTRIBUTING.md`**

```markdown
## Adding or modifying component variants

When you add, rename, or remove a variant on any component:

1. **Update the exported type union** in the component file
   (`export type NavigationAppearance = ...`).

2. **Add the variant to `APPEARANCE_VARIANTS`** (or equivalent constant)
   in `src/app/playground/<component>/page.tsx`.

3. **Run `pnpm check:playground`** before opening a PR.
   CI will fail the `lint` job if a variant is undocumented.

> The check is structural — it reads the TypeScript union directly,
> so renaming a variant without updating the playground is caught
> at type-check time, not at code review.
```

---

## Principle

**Every variant definition must have a corresponding playground entry, enforced by the type system and CI, not by memory.**

The fix works in three layers:

| Layer | Mechanism | Catches |
|---|---|---|
| **Type system** | `satisfies NavigationAppearance[]` in playground | Missing variant at compile time |
| **CI script** | `check-playground-coverage.ts` | Playground file missing entirely |
| **Process** | `CONTRIBUTING.md` rule | Human awareness before the PR |

This eliminates the per-feedback chase permanently — the build itself becomes the documentation enforcer.
